article.description: Davidson hit a season-high 18 3-pointers and easily beat Fordham 79-49 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Davidson hits 18 3-pointers, beats Fordham 79-49
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Davidson hit a season-high 18 3-pointers and easily beat Fordham 79-49 on Tuesday night. Mike Jones led the Wildcats with 15 points on five 3-pointers. Carter Collins added three 3-pointers. Kellan Grady had 13 points for Davidson (12-11, 6-5 Atlantic 10 Conference), which earned its fourth straight home victory. Luka Brajkovic added 12 points. Chris Austin had 11 points for the Rams (7-16, 1-10), who have now lost five consecutive games. Joel Soriano added nine rebounds. The Wildcats improve to 2-0 against the Rams this season. Davidson defeated Fordham 74-62 on Jan. 19. Davidson faces Saint Bonaventure on the road on Friday. Fordham plays Duquesne at home on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
